main event: Multiple unidentified flying objects were observed over South Fork Meadow, California on June 29, 1957.
interesting points: The objects were large, light-colored, and appeared to move erratically, similar to a cigar-shaped or triangular object.
One object was larger than the other five objects observed.
It was not possible to determine the actual altitude, speed, or direction of flight of the objects.
The objects were observed between 9:45 p.m. and 10:15 p.m.
The objects were observed by the United States Forest Service.
sighted object: six light-colored unidentified flying objects, one larger than the others
